<subSubSection id="B5977EB0691C76582B81D7B42D92E750" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E3177986B0EE5569FE5F3B823F0F4C7C" pageNumber="1">
Members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0C55FF418EA7F56009F121ECDF04A0DB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
are small erethistid catfishes traditionally diagnosed by a strongly depressed head and body and the presence of diverging serrations (antrorse on the distal half and retrorse on the proximal half) on the anterior edge of the pectoral spine. The genus, known from the sub-Himalayan region of the Indian subcontinent, currently includes two nominal species: 
<taxonomicName id="4812AD594BD6A2EA29A14989ED6DA710" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F07A5213-8D5F-40C8-ACB7-2CB6B1268D20" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides montana Hora 1950:191" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">E. montana Hora</taxonomicName>
, 1950 and 
<taxonomicName id="0578A169F81F3CB597E0A7FAF1C878D2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A4956CC4-3569-46C7-BE2E-37885905CA2D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides montana pipri Hora 1950:193" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pipri">E. pipri (Hora</taxonomicName>
, 1950).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="57C0ED4B40973075B3C6FCD3CA957DD5" pageNumber="1">
During a recent ichthyological survey of the northern Bengal region in India, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="B41C912119A4F803BD8342F87BD64368" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
were obtained, which upon further study, proved to be an undescribed species. The species is described here as 
<taxonomicName id="3ADF3C3AE46267AAC2886150E599A5A7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:439BE4CD-38E1-4064-967E-FD6A36F79871" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides sicula Ng 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sicula">Erethistoides sicula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E4F255DBF8925E8F327EBBE66B85FB60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. It was also found that the traditional diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="2E870EEEBC00AA44D5FA8667D6673593" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
is inadequate due to variation in the morphology of the pectoral-spine serrations. Here, four new synapomorphies diagnosing 
<taxonomicName id="18107D9AB0792E7B1FF7F909F8C52395" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
are identified and briefly discussed.
</paragraph>
